{"type":"message","id":"f70f48a4","parentId":"ad8d71a2","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:13:14.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log doesn't show the full error. The midscene computer command needs model configuration (API key, model name, base URL, etc.) to work. Let me check if there's a .env file or ask the user about the configuration.\n\nLooking at the SKILL.md, it says:\n```\nMIDSCENE_MODEL_API_KEY=\"your-api-key\"\nMIDSCENE_MODEL_NAME=\"model-name\"\nMIDSCENE_MODEL_BASE_URL=\"https://...\"\nMIDSCENE_MODEL_FAMILY=\"family-identifier\"\n```\n\nThese environment variables must be configured. Let me check if they exist in the workspace.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b8776cb219bb44c4a9b01cf8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"if (Test-Path .env) { Get-Content .env } else { \"No .env file found\" }"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qwen3-max","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":32143,"output":316,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32459,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772421178243}}
